<task id="024" project="email-communication-solution-r3">
  <metadata>
    <title>View mode — read-only display of existing sprk_communication record</title>
    <phase>Wave 1 — Engine + Wrappers + Sub-Components</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>3</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>020</dependencies>
    <blocks>028</blocks>
    <tags>react, frontend, communication, fluent-ui</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>View mode is the default Code Page surface (Form Component Control swap per FR-19); user-facing immutability + a11y of read-only display + transition-to-edit logic carry visibility risk. FULL appropriate.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>F</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <fr-refs>FR-10</fr-refs>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Implement `view` mode behavior in `EmailComposer/modes/viewMode.ts` (pure logic) + integration in `EmailComposer.tsx`.

    Behavior (FR-10):
    - Engine receives `sourceRecord: IComposerSourceRecord` (loaded by SendEmailPage wrapper or programmatic prop)
    - State derives entirely from sourceRecord — From, To, Cc, Subject, Body, Attachments, Associations all read-only
    - All sub-components render in read-only / disabled state:
      * RecipientField — Tags rendered as non-removable, no input field
      * BodyEditor — rendered as static HTML/text display (no editor toolbar, no contentEditable)
      * AttachmentList — list rendered, no Add buttons, no remove buttons; attachment names are LINKS to download the driveItem (via existing SPE facade)
      * ComposerActionBar — view-mode action set (Edit / Reply / Forward / Close per task 019)
    - No validation (record is immutable from the user's perspective)
    - Transition behaviors:
      * "Edit" action (per UQ2: may not be enabled depending on owner decision; spec ships with view = strictly read-only; Edit button rendered but disabled with tooltip explaining "Sent records are immutable") — when enabled, transitions engine state to `compose` mode keeping all fields populated
      * "Reply" action → transitions engine to `reply` mode (task 025 logic kicks in)
      * "Forward" action → transitions engine to `forward` mode (task 026 logic kicks in)
      * "Close" action → fires `onClose` callback if provided (Code Page handles navigation)

    Files:
    - `modes/viewMode.ts` (NEW) — pure functions: `deriveViewState(sourceRecord): Partial<EmailComposerState>`, `viewToEditTransition(state): Partial<EmailComposerState>`
    - Update `EmailComposer.reducer.ts` — handle `SET_MODE` action with mode-specific logic from view
    - Update `EmailComposer.tsx` — when `mode === 'view'`, render sub-components in read-only mode (passes `readOnly` prop or wraps in a `<ReadOnlyContext.Provider>`)
    - Update `RecipientField.tsx`, `BodyEditor.tsx`, `AttachmentList.tsx` to honor a `readOnly` prop
  </prompt>

  <role>
    React + TypeScript developer comfortable with mode-state-machine + read-only-render patterns.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `view` mode renders sourceRecord as read-only. No editable controls. Action buttons trigger correct mode transitions or callbacks. Attachments are downloadable links. `npm run build` + `npm run lint` clean.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per FR-10 + FR-19: view mode is the default surface when a user opens an existing `sprk_communication` record via the Form Component Control. Replaces the auto-generated Dataverse standard form (which is retained as admin fallback per NFR-07).

      Per UQ2: spec ships with view mode = strictly read-only. Edit button rendered but disabled. If owner later decides Edit IS allowed for sent records, the engine already has the transition logic — just enable the button.
    </background>
