  <steps>
    <step order="1">Author `modes/viewMode.ts`:
      - `deriveViewState(sourceRecord: IComposerSourceRecord): Partial&lt;EmailComposerState&gt;` — maps sourceRecord fields → state slots
      - `viewToEditTransition(state): Partial&lt;EmailComposerState&gt;` — flips mode to `compose`, keeps all fields; for UQ2 future use</step>
    <step order="2">Update `EmailComposer.reducer.ts`:
      - `initialState` handles `mode === 'view' &amp;&amp; sourceRecord` by applying `deriveViewState`
      - `SET_MODE` action handles view → reply/forward/edit transitions</step>
    <step order="3">Update sub-components (`RecipientField`, `BodyEditor`, `AttachmentList`) to honor `readOnly` prop:
      - RecipientField: render Tags only, no input field
      - BodyEditor: render `&lt;div dangerouslySetInnerHTML={{__html: sanitizedHtml}}&gt;` for html OR `&lt;pre&gt;{text}&lt;/pre&gt;` for plaintext; no toolbar, no editor
      - AttachmentList: render rows with download links (anchor pointing to existing SPE facade GET endpoint with the driveItemId); no Add/Remove buttons</step>
    <step order="4">Update `EmailComposer.tsx` to compute `isReadOnly = mode === 'view'` and pass to all sub-components.</step>
    <step order="5">Wire view-mode action buttons (ComposerActionBar) to mode transitions:
      - Edit → dispatch `SET_MODE` to `compose` (button DISABLED per UQ2; tooltip explains)
      - Reply → dispatch `SET_MODE` to `reply` (task 025 logic handles pre-fill)
      - Forward → dispatch `SET_MODE` to `forward` (task 026)
      - Close → invoke `props.onClose?.()`</step>
    <step order="6">Smoke test in dev: load a sample record, all sub-components read-only, Reply transitions to reply mode (visible as subject prefix change once task 025 lands).</step>
    <step order="7">Run `npm run build` + `npm run lint` clean.</step>
    <step order="7.5">Step 9.5 quality gates — code-review + adr-check.</step>
    <step order="8">Update `TASK-INDEX.md`: 024 ✅.</step>
    <step order="9">Update `current-task.md` per task-execute protocol.</step>
  </steps>

